CRITICAL IMAGE PROMPT RULE:
- Stable Diffusion models are trained on Danbooru dataset
- ONLY use Danbooru tags from the Allowed Keywords list below
- NEVER invent new tags or use general photography terms not in Danbooru
- FORBIDDEN examples: "medium shot" (0 posts), "bust shot" (incorrect term)
- FORBIDDEN environment tags: "dark_room", "high_contrast_shadow", "cinematic_shadows", "glowing_screen", "projector_screen" (produce monotonous/dark results)
- SAFE examples: "cowboy shot" (729K posts), "upper body" (1.01M posts), "full_body" (892K posts)

CRITICAL TAG FORMAT RULES:
- ALWAYS use underscores, NEVER spaces: "thumbs_up" ✓, "thumbs up" ✗
- NEVER combine multiple adjectives into one tag: "short green hair" ✗
- SEPARATE attributes into individual tags: "short_hair, green_hair" ✓
- Copy tag format EXACTLY from Allowed Keywords list (with underscores)

CRITICAL STYLE CONSISTENCY RULE:
- Visual Style "{{ style }}" MUST be applied to ALL scenes consistently
- If style is "chibi", add "chibi" tag to EVERY scene
- If style is "realistic", do NOT add chibi/water_color/sketch tags
- For "chibi" style, always use: "chibi, super_deformed, small_body, big_head" ✓

Instructions:
1. Create a **natural conversation** between Speaker A and Speaker B. This is a DIALOGUE, not a monologue.
   - Target: {{ ((duration / 3) | round | int) }}-{{ ((duration / 2) | round | int) }} scenes for {{ duration }} seconds
   - Each scene duration: set to 3 (backend auto-calculates based on script reading time)
2. **STRICT ALTERNATION**: A, B, A, B, A, B... Each scene's speaker MUST alternate.
   - Speaker A gets roughly half the scenes, Speaker B gets the rest.
   - Narrator scenes are RARE (max 1) — keep focus on A↔B back-and-forth.
   - ❌ FORBIDDEN: Two consecutive scenes with the same speaker (e.g., A, A).
   - ✅ REQUIRED: Every script line must be ADDRESSED TO or RESPONDING TO the other character.
   - ❌ BAD script: "와, 여기 너무 예쁘다!" (talking to self — this is monologue, not dialogue)
   - ✅ GOOD script: "야, 이거 봐! 완전 영화 속 장면 같지 않아?" (talking to the other person)
3. Each single scene's image shows ONLY the current speaker (1girl or 1boy).
